inn1.comm: starts off with a delivery slipping towards middle and leg, Gambhir leans forward to work it past square leg
walks down the track and this is just the second ball of the game. But no predetermined slog, he sees the ball is on a length and coming into him and pushes to covers
pushes this one through the off-stump channel and Gambhir lets it fly past him
Another walk down the track. Reaches out for a full delivery and flicks it along the ground to the square leg boundary.
leans forward to drive a full length delivery on the off and middle back down the track

Wary of Gambhir walking down the track, Sohail hurls this short but offers width outside off stump. Gambhir stays at his original position and upper cuts it over backward point. One bounce and over the ropes.
Short of length, outside the off stump and Sehwag cuts to backward point
drifting towards the pads, Sehwag misses out on it but will pick a leg bye
good delivery. It landed on a length around middle and off and moved away from Gambhir who left it alone
further outside off stump, Gambhir plants his right foot across, covers the off stump and shoulders arms
just outside off stump, Gambhir taps it gently towards backward point, one look at Sehwag and they take off for the single
drifts down leg, Sarfraz makes a diving half-stop. Gambhir calls over Sehwag for a quick run.
back of length, just outside off stump, straightens a touch, Sehwag mistimes a punch-drive back down the track
outside the off stump, no movement and Gambhir runs it down to third man
lands on a length but outside leg stump, moves towards leg and Sehwag clips it wide of long leg for couple of runs.
shifts his line to the off and middle, full in length and Sehwag drives to mid-off
back of length, just outside off stump, cut to backward point
on a length, angling away from Sehwag who punches it to covers.
on the off stump, back of length and Sehwag stays adjacent to the line and dabs it to backward point.

almost a run out. It was edged to Tanvir at that wide leg slip, Sehwag calls him over for a single and Gambhir responds but is a touch late as he was initially ball watching and Tanvir's throw misses the sticks at the non-striker's end. Gambhir was just short of the crease
full in length, just outside the off stump, straightens, Sehwag thinks it will come in,  bat pushes inside the line and edge through gully region
charges down the track and tries to pull a short of length delivery but misses to connect
on a length, on the middle and leg stump line, tucked past the square-leg region
cuts in towards middle and off stump line, pushed down the track
just outside the off stump, turned to backward point region
down leg side. Another wide.
blasted to deep point boundary. It was short in length and well outside off as well, Sehwag rocked back to cut it through the off-side field
And Sehwag square drives to him. This delivery was fuller but again some width offered outside off
length delivery around the off stump, Gambhir taps it to right of backward point for a single
Wallop. Sehwag hits a full delivery through the line. Up up and over long-on.
But, with the fine leg up, he drifts down leg and Sehwag flicks it past the fielder. Easy pickings.
played towards point for a single
There is the Gambhir charge. Time and again he does this against the seamers. Rauf pushed it across him and he got a thick edge to third man boundary
fuller, on a length, around middle and off, straightens and Gambhir defends
back of length, outside off stump, forced to third man. Slight fumble but the fielder recovers.
whipped through midwicket. It was on the middle and off stump line, but very full in length and Sehwag wristed it through the on side
Another whipped flick and this time towards long leg
short in length and well outside the off stump, short of length and cut hard through backward point
walks down the track and taps a length delivery to backward point
on a length, on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
superb stroke. He went back to a back-of-length delivery on the off and middle and punched it through wide mid-on region. Lovely timing.
There he goes again. Sehwag is having a party. Too short  and Sehwag rocked back to pull it over midwicket.
shifts his line to outside off, punched to covers.
Gambhir hands over the strike back to Sehwag. He tapped the ball gently, it rolled behind the stumps and they rushed across for a quick single
cuts in off a length, into the middle stump line, Sehwag is cramped up by the nip-backer and jabs it to the on side
Oh he was going after this one as well. It was a length delivery outside off and Sehwag cleared the front leg and tried to smash it on the up but mistimed it down the track past the bowler
another quick single. This time to right of backward point. Sehwag called quickly and Gambhir responded immediately

wonderfully played. He knew Rauf was cutting them back in, so he moved towards middle and off, got almost outside the line of a delivery coming in towards middle and punched it sweetly through the on side.
So Rauf gets this to shape in towards off stump, Sehwag is on the middle and drives to covers.
skips down the track, tries to flat-bat a short-of-length delivery outside off but the ball keeps a tad low and rushes under the blade.
stays back to punch a length delivery through cover point for a single

shout for lbw as the bowler thinks it hit the pad first. It cut back in towards the middle and off, Sehwag went back to cut and it did hit the pad first before running of the bat to third man. Lucky escape there. It would have crashed into middle and off. It hit the left pad and then went on to hit the bat but umpire Ian Gould didn't pick it up.
goes back to to push to backward point for a single

hit  just over mid-off. Sehwag stayed back to mistime a lofted shot just over Tanvir. Rameez Raja is fuming on air. He reckons Tanvir could have put more effort and taken the catch. Tanvir had turned around slowly and didn't show much urgency in getting to the ball
cuts back in, worked to square leg
another quick single. Gambhir leans forward to place a length delivery close on the off side. Sehwag is back on strike.
slower one, full and on the middle stump line, Sehwag cleared the front foot and chipped it towards deep square leg
runs down the track and drives inside-out to left of sweeper cover for couple of runs.
lands it short of length outside leg, moves it towards leg and middle, tucked behind square leg for a single.

Sehwag moved towards the off stump, lifted his left leg and lapped a short of length delivery from outside off to deep backward square leg boundary. He had predetermined that. He was seen playing this particular shot quite a few times in IPL. The bowlers would try to cramp him for room by cutting the ball back into him and he would, suddenly, walk towards off to play it behind square leg.
just outside off stump, holding its line, tries to dab it to third man and is beaten
leans forward to push a full length delivery towards wide mid-off for a single. They waited to see whether the extra-cover fielder manages to cut it; he didn't and off they went
drifts a full delivery towards middle and leg, turned to long leg

Caught at covers by Afridi. Gambhir had come down the track, as is his wont, and flashed a length delivery inside-out to covers. The bat-handle turned a bit in his hands and he couldn't clear the fielder
leans forward to defend a full-length delivery on the middle and off. Takes a walk towards square leg, looks around the field, takes a deep breath and is now ready to face the next ball
banged in short, at the rib cage, clipped to fine leg for a single
on the middle and leg, flicked to deep square leg

huge shout for a catch behind decision and after consultation with the square leg umpire it has been referred to third umpire. It is a clean catch. Sehwag tried to dab a length delivery outside off stump to third man and it ran off the face of the bat.

Catch the highlights of Sehwag's breezy knock later on in the day. Click here. [Only for USA viewers]
gets off the mark with a push to wide mid-on
hits the deck short of length and rushing through the off-stump channel, left alone
gets behind the line of a length delivery and pushes it back down the track
short of length, on the middle and leg, turned to the on side. "That's the better line boy," says Sarfraz.

Another wicket goes down. Pakistan roar back into the game. It was dug in short and Raina went for the pull but had to fetch it from outside off and top edged it to Salman at deep midwicket region.  Raina had jumped to defend the last two deliveries but decided to go after this one. Enter Dhoni.
goes back to push to the off side.
leans forward to work a fuller delivery through wide midwicket
turned to midwicket region
cuts in towards middle and off, edged back to the pad.
another inside-edge on to the pad  as the ball shapes in towards middle and off. Wasim Akram, on air, reckons it has started to reverse swing already.

big shout for a catch behind decision but it had gone off the chest. It was a well-directed short-pitched delivery, Dhoni hopped but made sure he dropped his wrists and got his bat out of the way and it bounded off the chest to the 'keeper. Where is Brian Close?! He would have nodded in appreciation.
leans forward to defend a delivery on the off stump line
lands on a length on the leg stump line, cuts towards middle, worked to the on side
leans forward to defend a length delivery on the off and middle line.
pushes a length delivery past the bowler
short in length, cutting in, turned to long leg
back of length, around middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket region for a single
lifting delivery outside off stump and Yuvraj drops his wrists and sways away from the line. Akram wants a slip in. No one there at the moment.
Another bouncer, this time at the right shoulder and Yuvraj ducks towards off to evade that one. Great contest on
leans forward to defend a length delivery
breaks free with a fierce punch through the off side. Short and width offered, Yuvraj cashed in.
straighter and defended
gets forward to push a length delivery past the bowler and between mid-on and mid-off for a single
length delivery outside off, punched to mid-off. Yuvraj turns towards square leg and practises hitting it in the V again.
Sweetly timed boundary. He thrust his front foot out and it was the length delivery but he punched it on the up and through the line and to the straight boundary.
forces this one through wide mid-on region for couple of runs. Will the next one be a bouncer?
it's the fuller length delivery, shaping away outside off, punched to mid-off.
Pull of  the front foot. Blink. The ball is into the midwicket stands. Not all that short but he went for it. Akram drools,"I haven't seen many players play like that, of the front foot."
fuller and outside off stump, dabbed to backward point
on the middle and leg line, worked to right of midwicket for a single
fullish, around the off stump, pushed to covers.
another full delivery around the off stump and Yuvraj places this one to right of mid-off for couple of runs
straighter and Yuvraj whips it from the off stump line to mid-on. He then suggests he should have hit it much straighter.

Fabulous straight punch-drive. He had practiced it after the last ball and executed it now. It was a length delivery on the middle and off and he timed it very well. The front elbow was high and the bat came down straight.
leans forward to turn a fuller delivery to wide midwicket region for a single
Edged through the vacant slip region . Akram had said put a man in there and we know why now. It was a length delivery shaping away from Yuvraj who stabbed it off the outer edge.
full and straight, driven to mid-on
a tad slower but Yuvraj picked it up very well and punched it on the up through wide mid-off. There were five men inside the circle on the off and he picked the gap very well.
on the middle and leg, worked through square leg
drifts towards the pads, Dhoni shovels it towards the short-fine leg fielder. It was in the air briefly but fell well short of the man.
gets back and across to push a length delivery to covers
short in length, moving from middle and leg towards middle, pushed to midwicket

Sarfraz takes a flying catch. Yuvraj has to head back to the hutch. Yuvraj tried to late cut a short-of-length delivery leaving him, got a thick edge and Sarfraz flew to his left to take the catch. Super stuff from the man who has replaced Kamran Akmal. Yuvraj had not moved his feet; he just bent the back leg and tried to steer it. Fatal.
short of length, cutting away from Rohit who pushes it to extra cover.
back of length, just outside the off stump, defended down the track.
beaten by a lovely delivery that left him late. Very late. He was going back to defend a full length delivery. Mistake no 1. And then he tried to chase the ball as it cut away from him. Mistake no 2.

More trouble. He thrust his front foot across and wanted to let the length delivery go through to the 'keeper. But he was late in getting the bat out of the way and it ran off the face of the bat to the off side.
slider on the middle stump line, Dhoni makes sure he doesn't get his front leg across and dabs the ball behind square leg.
fuller, almost a yorker, Rohit, unlike Dhoni, presses his front leg across, then has to pull it back in a hurry and digs it to wide mid-on
leans forward to push a  loopy delivery to covers
will get a single with a push to extra cover region
slows up the pace, tosses it bit more air, keeps it really full, driven through the mid-off region
googly and Dhoni lunges forward, gets his bat way ahead of his pad to defend
sharp bouncer on the middle and leg line, Rohit is late on the pull and the ball flies over the flashing blade.
leans forward to defend a full delivery
on the middle stump line, turned to the leg side
turned to the leg side for a single.
run down to third man for a single.
on the off and middle, forced to covers where Misbah makes the stop
fuller and pushed to Misbah.
gets down the track to drive to long-on. "Bahut aala Shahid bhai," says Sarfraz. [Very good]
punches it to long-off
skips down the track to squeeze a full delivery to short fine leg
stretches forward to drive to long-off for a single
leans forward to flick a full delivery to square leg
turns down leg, worked to fine leg region
leans forward to defend but the ball turns past the prod and strikes him high on the left thigh.
full and driven to long-off
on the middle and leg, worked to the on side for a single
again turning into middle and leg, squeezed to square leg
leans forward to push to midwicket
short in length and well outside the off stump, Rohit Sharma goes on the back foot and steers it through backward point.
slower through the air, goes right back to punch to long-on
well outside the off stump, full, Dhoni reaches out to chop it to short third man region
full and outside off, driven to long-off
loopy delivery outside off stump, Dhoni lunges to drive to deep cover.
comes down the track, Ajmal drags back the length and it is turned behind square leg
spins towards the middle and leg, worked to backward square leg
leans forward to defend a delivery spinning into middle
on the leg and middle stump line, tries to sweep and it runs off the pad to the on side. Sarfraz picks the ball up.
lands on middle and off, spins in, punched to long-on
full and Dhoni stretches forward to on drive to long-on
leans forward to push through the on side
driven to long-on for a single
gets forward to push a full delivery to long-on
almost gone. Rohit Sharma opted for the slog sweep and got a bottom edge to short fine leg region. Afridi thought he had his man there and holds his head as he watches the ball clip the edge.
leans forward to push to covers
on the middle and leg, swept down to long leg.
The doosra. It landed on the middle and leg, Dhoni thought it would turn in and tried to play towards the on side and got a leading edge to the off side.
the off break and turned to fine leg
on the leg and middle, swept to long leg.
the off break and turned to fine leg
on the middle, turning in, nudged to on side
leans forward to drive to covers
goes back to turn a short-of-length delivery from outside off to deep midwicket
comes down the track, nudges to midwicket region
long hop outside off, edges a pull shot to midwicket.
loopy delivery well outside the off stump, driven to Misbah at extra cover
goes back to turn a slider to backward square leg region
turns from middle to leg, Dhoni backs away to the leg side to punch it to longon
moves outside leg and cuts a floateron middle and off to deep point
doosra on the middle and leg line, Dhoni went right back to defend to on side
spins sharply from middle stump line but goes down leg side.
doosra outside off this time, Dhoni is late to pick it up and cuts to deep point
goes back to turn a delivery turning in past square leg\
turns towards the pad, tucked to backward square leg
goes back to cut a short delivery to wide of sweeper cove
leans forward to drive to sweeper cover
lunges forward to again ping the deep cover
rocks back to pull a short delivery to midwicket boundary
the doosra, from back of the hand, Dhoni doesn't pick it again and ends up swatting it down the track
leans forward to drive to extra cover
backs outside leg and dabs a delivery turning to the leg stump line to midwicket. Misbah with the throw which is a tad wide and by the time the bowler collected and broke the stumps, Rohit was in
on the middle stump, turns sharply to the leg side and again Dhoni dabs to midwicket
doosra on the middle and leg line. Dhoni picked that one and defends to the on side
turns past square leg for a single
outside the off stump, skids on and Rohit chops it to the off side
fuller and Rohit drives to deep cover
short in length outside off and skidding on straight, Dhoni goes back to cut it through backward point for a boundary. His first one.
stretches well forward to drive a length delivery to long-off
turns away from Rohit who cuts to short third man
punches this one to long-on for a single.
square driven through cover point for a single
lands outside off stump, short and holding its line, Dhoni went back to smash it to extra-cover boundary.
leans forward to defend a full delivery to the off side
spins towards the leg stump line, nudged to the on side
similar line, dabbed behind square leg for a single
moves outside leg stump and square drives a full delivery on the stumps to sweeper cover.
well outside the off stump, left alone
loopy delivery full and on the middle, driven to long-off
quicker, shorter, turns away, cut to point
sweeps from well outside off to long-on for a single
fullish, driven hard but straight to Misbah at cover
leans forward to drive a delivery around off to covers
just outside off stump, on a length, punched to covers.
back of length, angled across Rohit who cuts it to right of wide third man for couple of runs
slips down leg side and tickled to long leg for a single
short in length, angling towards middle and off, Dhoni goes right back to turn it past square leg
walks down the track, Tanvir hurls it on the leg stump line, worked to long leg
short in length and slanted across Rohit stood tall to punch it on the up through extra cover. Looked good.
well outside the off stump, full, driven powerfully to sweeper cover
yorker length outside off, Rohit tries to chop it away but can't connect
the slider on the middle and Rohit brings his bat down in a hurry to push it back down the track
unfurls the slog sweep and will pick up couple of runs to wide long-on region
outside the off stump, goes too hard at the drive and mistimes it to covers
flatter, quicker, pushed to the off side and Afridi fields
From round the stumps, coming in towards middle, defended to covers.
short in length, well outside the off stump, Dhoni can't reach it with his cut shot.
leans forward to push a length delivery towards mid-on and runs with the stroke
moves close to the line to push a length delivery to covers
banged in short and wide of the off stump, Rohit cuts to sweeper cover.
walks towards the off stump and punches to long-off
wide outside off stump.
again well outside off, Dhoni lets it go. Not wide enough to be called wide, though
had enough of leaving deliveries, charges out and drills a full delivery to right of long-off
leans forward to drive to covers
on the off stump line, pushed to the off side
on the off stump line. Dhoni stays still on the leg stump and punches it to Misbah at extra cover
just outside off, keeps a touch low, squeezed to short third man
length delivery outside off, from round the stumps, Rohit edges the off drive to midwicket
from wide of the crease, short in length and outside off, forced to long-off
full and just outside off stump, driven to long-off
moving towards off stump, eased to long-off for a single
fullish, on the off stump line, Dhoni doesn't move his feet but just drives through the line to long-off
slower one, pretty short in length, Rohit waits before dabbing it to third man
short in length, on the off and middle line, shaping in a touch, worked past square leg
back of length, outside off stump, driven to deep cover. 21st ODI fifty for Dhoni and the 100 of the partnership is up as well.
Rohit brings up his fourth ODI fifty with a dab to third man.
full pitched on middle and leg, driven to Afridi at long-on
on the off stump line, full in length, pushed to extra cover
dropped by the bowler. It was the slower one and Rohit was early into his drive. Rao lunged but couldn't hold on.
turns to the leg stump line, worked towards midwicket
flat, on that middle and leg line again - he has repeatedly pinged that line today - turned past square leg
moves outside leg, the ball too was turning outside leg but Rohit punches it to right of backward point.
the doosra and Rohit misses the sweep shot  and is struck on the back pad. It was turning past the off, though.
drives to long-on for a single
beaten by the doosra. Delivered from the back of the hand, full and outside off, Dhoni has no clue, has a waft and is beaten
moves outside leg even as he comes down the track and on drives to long-on
full and outside off stump, Dhoni edges the intended big drive to the midwicket region
Done in by the head-high bouncer. Rohit Sharma was standing outside the crease and skied his pull to deep square leg region.
short in length outside off stump, cut to right of sweeper cover. Again that bottom-hand works over time.
short in length, coming towards middle and off, nudged to the on side for a quick single. Rao rushes after the ball and nudges Yusuf on the shoulder as both converge at the other end
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
low full toss well outside the off stump, thrashed to wide long-off.
turning into middle and leg line, worked to deep midwicket.
dropped by Ajmal. It was driven hard to him and he should have taken that. The fielding has been pretty poor in this tournament. By most teams.
turned to midwicket

First ODI wicket for Ajmal. Does Yusuf in by the doosra. It was on the middle and leg, Yusuf tried to loft it over the on side but it broke away and flew off the edge to long-off. Ajmal, who had just dropped    YK, rushed towards Sarfraz to celebrate his special moment.
short in length, pushed to covers
edged to third man. Full and outside off, Irfan pushed inside the line and it ran off the outer edge. 250 up for India.
on the middle and leg line, turned to midwicket for a single
homing in on the off stump, punched to deep point region for a single
rocks back to force a length delivery on off to right of deep cover
a tad slower and Dhoni mistimes the drive back to the bowler. He then suggests he should have wristed it across the line
just outside off, cut with the spin to backward point

the doosra turned in to Irfan's surprise who didn't pick it up, was cramped, tried to get his bat down in a hurry, it went off the gloves on to top of the flap of the pad and went past Sarfraz. And it has been given a bye. Hmm...
worked to square leg for a single
another doosra, stabbed off the inner edge to square leg
loopy delivery on the middle, driven to the bowler
turns in from short of length, on the middle, punched to long-off
stays back to force a length delivery on the off and middle to long-off
full one outside off, Irfan lofts it over extra cover. Yousuf with the chase and Afridi with the throw.
on the middle, from a length, wristed to deep midwicket region for couple of runs
full pitched outside off stump, driven to long off
pushes a single to extra cover
outside the off stump, back of length ,cut to deep point
yorker outside off stump, dug out to extra cover
comes down the track and drags it from outside off to deep midwicket
leans forward to push to cover point. So the big hitting has been left to Irfan
on the middle and leg, tries to turn to square leg, runs off the pad back down the track
They can't pick the doosra. The video guy in the Indian team is going to work over time today. It broke in, beats the waft and runs off the left thigh past Sarfraz
leans forward to drive to long-on
yorker on the leg stump line, squeezed off the pads to the point region
low full toss, flat-batted over covers
yorker length outside off stump, dug out to third man
full delivery, driven to long-on
slower one, on a length, drag pulls to deep midwicket
yorker length on the middle, whipped to deep midwicket
slog-pulls a short-of-length delivery from outside off to wide long-on boundary
low dipping full toss and Irfan slices it towards long-on. Dhoni is rushing for the second and reaches in time to beat the direct hit
another really full delivery, just short of the blockhole, jabbed to covers
slower one, well outside the off stump, Dhoni lets it go
Fast full toss on the leg side. Dhoni shovels it in the air towards square leg and Sarfraz rushes on, collides with Misbah, coming in from midwicket, but manages to hold on
full pitched, stabbed down the track
clears the front foot and drills a full pitched delivery to left of long-on
attempted yorker on the leg stump line, ends up a dipping full toss, nudged to square leg
Streaky edge to the third man boundary. He swung across the line and gets a profitable edge.
superbly struck down the ground. It was the low full toss, he bent his back knee to loft it over the bowler's head
slower one, carved to right of sweeper cover
full pitched on the off stump line, driven towards long-off for couple of runs
really full delivery, short of the blockhole, driven to long-on for a single . India end on a strong 308.

inn2.comm: short in length and well outside the off stump, left alone. Praveen inspects his landing area.
The chase is up and running. Swinging to the legs and Butt flicks it through square leg. There is a midwicket in and it raced well to the left of him
back of length, outside off stump, pushed to right of covers where Raina makes a diving half-stop. Rohit swoops on the ball and has a shy at the striker's ends, misses and they take the over throws
from round the stumps, on a length, around middle and off, pushed to mid-on
back over the wickets, full and on the middle stump line, hint of swing and driven back down the track, Praveen lunges to his right to deflect the ball towards mid-off
banged in short and pulled down and through the square-leg region
short in length, curving away from the off stump, punched to Gambhir at wide third man
Butt plays a similar shot and again Gambhir comes into play
beaten outside off stump. It was full and outside off stump, Nasir crouches, doesn't move his feet and has a waft at it
outside off stump, partly edged partly steered on the bounce to left of second slipper who deflects it towards backward point
again on that back of length, just outside off stump, mistimes a punch to the on side.
moves towards the line of a length delivery outside off and pushes it between short extra cover and mid-off
on the off stump line, skids on, pushed past the lunging short extra cover fielder and to mid-off
vey well cut. Not all that short, just outside off stump but Butt cuts it past point. The bottom-hand came off the handle as he played that stroke
goes for it again but mistimes it to point
slower, lands on a length on the middle, moves towards off and Butt defends down the track
crashed through covers. Full and well outside off, he drove it past the short extra cover fielder
angling across Salman, closer to the off stump, pushed to covers
129 kmph short-of-length delivery coming into Nasir who is cramped but short-arm pulls it to deep square leg region
128.7 kmph delivery just outside the off stump, steered to third man
and punched straight to that man there, close on the off side.
fuller, around off stump, pushed to Yuvraj at mid-off.
128.6 kmph bouncer on the middle and off line, Salman sways away from the line.
130.1 kmph length delivery outside off, pushed to covers.
clears the front foot and drives a length delivery on the up to mid-off
Nasir stands outside the crease and flashes a short-of-length delivery outside off to deep backward point boundary.
Smashed down the ground. Nasir is showing what he is capable off. He charged down the track and knifed a length delivery to right of mid-on
brings this one off the good length to middle and off, turned to the midwicket region
With the fine leg up, Praveen sends down a slower one down leg side and Nasir laps it past the fielder. Confident start to the run chase.
on the off stump line, steered to cover point
on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
bounces off a length, just outside off stump, Butt adjusted superbly to the extra bounce to force it through cover point
slower one, full and just outside off, turned to midwicket
on the off stump line, he wanted to punch it through wide mid-on and mistimes it to the on side of the pitch and towards mid-on
drifts towards middle and leg, whipped through midwicket. Akram reckons they should have run harder and got three. Kumar came around from long leg to make the stop
fuller, on middle, turned to deep square leg region where Praveen makes the stop
short in length, on the middle and leg, clipped to square leg and Chawla fields. Free hit coming up as Ishant overstepped
Butt stays still on the leg-stump line and drills a full pitched delivery on middle and leg  through wide mid-on region.
Runs are flowing here. Short of length and on the pads, clipped past the diving Chawla at square leg. Chawla is standing well to the right of the umpire as this is a slow track.
Salman loves the Indians. He goes down on his knee to cream a overpitched delivery through covers
dug in short of length, on the middle and leg, turned to long leg
wide down the leg side.
again short in length and on the pads, tucked to fine leg
shifts his line to the off stump and steered to cover point
Blasted down the ground. Nasir goes down the track, Irfan drags back the length but Nasir goes through the line, in the V, between the bowler and mid-off. Super strike.

fuller in length, around off, steered to right of backward point, Rohit swoops on the ball and has a shy at the striker's end. Had he hit Nasir would have been run out. He had set off for the single and was sent back by Butt
leans forward to defend a length delivery back down the track

Super pull shot, can't say the same about the effort from Ishant at deep square leg region. It was the head-high bouncer and Nasir pulled it down to the ground and Ishant moving to his right makes a right royal mess of it
fuller, around off, driven to mid-off

Oh what a mix up. Butt is run out. Agony for Pakistan while the Indians get into a huddle of joy. It was steered to left of third man and Gambhir fired in the throw. Butt had turned for the second, only to be sent back by his new opening partner and couldn't make it back in time.
short in length, cuts towards middle and leg, clipped to long leg
cuts in towards middle and off, defended to the off side
fuller, just outside the off, opens the bat-face and steers to third man
edged but falls midway between slips and Praveen at third man. Nasir had topedged the bouncer and Praveen seemed to have lost the ball in the back ground
on a length, around off stump, defended to the off side
short in length and outside off, Younis Khan whiplashed a square drive but Rohit moving to his left at point cuts it off.
charges down the track, tries to pull a delivery dug in short and edged it to third man. Steady boy steady!
full and outside off stump, Younis stretches across to square drive to right of Ishant at third man
fullish, angling away from Younis who mistimes a drive to Yusuf at short extra cover
another really full delivery outside off - they are hoping Younis would square drive one in the air and to a fielder - driven to third man
short-pitched delivery, Nasir swivels off the front foot to pull the head-high bouncer coming in to him to square leg boundary

above head-high bouncer, again coming in to Nasir who pulls and places it deep backward square leg boundary. Very well controlled shot. He had edged two pulls before but they were off the deliveries that were leaving him

cutting in to middle, turned to square leg. Younis then practices hitting it straight. Meanwhile, at the other end Nasir too is doing the same. The adrenalin rush is making them do the opposite on occasions.
leans forward to push a length delivery to the off side.
back of length, just outside off, Younis wants to punch it on the up but a touch extra bounce meant he mistimes it to covers
short in length ,shaping in from outside off, Younis goes back, stands tall and pushes it to point.
the slower one, Younis is made to wait and pushes to cover point.. He takes the helmet off, wipes the sweat of his forehead, dons the helmet again and plays the horizontal cut shot.
cutting in from back of length, towards the off stump, turned to midwicket. End of a very good over from the teenager.
full and on the middle, shaping in, he takes the front leg from the line and drives to mid-on
outside off stump, square driven to point.
full, on that middle stump line again, Nasir makes sure he doesn't get his front foot across, whips it in the air but well to the left of the mid-on fielder. He moves to 42
slipping towards middle and leg, wristed to square leg where Chawla makes a tumbling save
walks down the track and towards off but the intent is not violence but just a tap to the off side for a single.
outside the off stump, guided to left of Gambhir at third man
on the middle stump line, from short of length, worked to long leg for a single
Short. Wide. Upper cut. Crashes to the point boundary. He hit deliberately up and over. And what's more Younis has a free hit coming up. Here we go.
moves towards the off stump, Ishant sends a slower one, full and on the off and middle and Younis swings it to deep square leg region

short in length, outside off stump, Younis goes for the pull but mistimes it to mid-on. He then practises the pull shot again and also, the on-the-up extra cover drive. Since it was outside off, the latter would be a better shot
beaten on the cut. It rushed past the off stump and Younis wanted to punch it through point but missed
leans forward to push to extra cover
another short of length delivery outside off stump, sweetly timed punch to right of point and Rohit makes a diving half-stop
full and on the off stump line, pushed to the off side. Praveen makes the stumps, turns and threatens to throw at the striker's end and the crowd roar
walks to the off stump line, Praveen hurls it to his right and it is steered to backward point
slower one, cutting away from Younis who is beaten on the forward prod.
back of length, just outside off stump, guided to point
short and well outside off, cut hard but straight to point fielder.
fuller and driven to mid-off. Maiden over. Drinks break.
around the off stump line, steered to backward point
short of length, slanted across Nasir who guides it to third man
short of length, just outside off, punched to point
on the middle and off and he swatted it across the line to long leg. Ishant smiles. Younis too has a laugh.
on the middle and leg, turned to right of square leg for a single.
walks outside off, Ishant hurls it further outside off, steered to third man. 100 up for Pakistan.
lovely extra-cover drive. Full and outside off, he leaned into the shot superbly.
outside off, slashed to third man
short in length, outside off, pulled straight to Sehwag at midwicket
slower delivery, fullish on his pads, worked away square
another one on his pads and he misses out again as his punch doesn't beat mid-on
full, turned to midwicket, another dot ball
length delivery on off, clipped away towards wide mid-on
another length delivery, a bit of width this time, guided by Younis towards third man
back of a length, on his leg , pushed to mid-on
outside off, tries to run down to third man, misses
That's his fifty. Third ODI and first against India. He pulled a short of length delivery from outside off past Sehwag at midwicket. Well played young man.
leans forward to steer to point
outside off, punched to the off side
slower one, turned to mid-on
shortish, on middle and leg, Jamshed attempts to smash that to midwicket, gets only a single
fuller delivery outside off, Younis rather cheekily sweeps that to fine leg
slower delivery, on a length and a bit outside Jamshed's off stump, he tries to dab it to third man but is beaten
back of a length, on off, played back to the bowler
a bit of a loop, again back of a length, but on his pads and that worked to mid-on
swept from outside off by Younis
hit to midwicket for a single

flat, on a length outside off, Jamshed plays it towards point, go for a quick single , the throw came in at the non-striker's end but Nasir reaches in time but he is down on the ground now. Cramps. The physio is out there.
Younis resumes play with a feisty cut to point boundary.
on the off stump line, full, punched to sweeper cover
long hop and Younis, who has really dominated Chawla in the recent encounters, rocks back to smash it to midwicket boundary. 5000 runs for Younis Khan
leans forward to steer to cover point
leans forward to defend a full delivery
googly, quick and flat, worked to midwicket region
just outside off, slower through the air, pushed to covers
floated outside off, full, pushed to the onside
just outside off, keeps a touch low, short in length and Yousuf goes back to punch it through the backward point region and Irfan makes a diving stop near the ropes
The reverse sweep is out. Younis is such a good player against spin. He stretched forward and paddled a reverse sweep well to the left of short third man
leans forward to drive to long-on
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
turns in towards middle and off, forced off the back foot to deep cover
stretches forward to drive to covers
drives to deep extra cover
full and outside off, swept to long leg
short and well outside off, dabbed to backward point
loopy delivery well outside off, driven to deep cover
leans forward to drive down the pitch and Chawla dives to make the stop.
slow through the air, turns towards middle and leg, worked past square leg for a single
backs away to cut a short-of-length delivery turning in to sweeper cover
the drifter and Yousuf is beaten , trying to guide it through vacant slip region
gets forward to drive to long-on
full , lands just outside off and whipped to long-on
Yousuf plays the reverse sweep but hits it straight to short third man.
forces this one through the on side

short in length, turning away outside off and Yousuf cuts and cuts well. A four to deep backward point boundary. There was a backward point and a short third man and he delayed the shot to find the gap between them
slider on the middle and off, defended
on the middle and leg, nudged to short fine leg region for a quick single
leans forward to drive to long-off

again short and well outside off, Yousuf cuts to the right of the backward point fielder and Ishant moving to his left fails to cut it off near the ropes. Chawla has been superbly dominated by the Pakistani batsmen in the recent times. Today is going the same way. Let's see if he can come back strongly
leans forward to drive to right of long-on and that is his fifty. No 35.
turns in towards off, guided through cover point for a single
stretches forward to drive to long-on
turns in towards the off, Yousuf tries to guide it to cover point but the sharp turn beats the waft and it bounds off the inner thigh past Dhoni
Another reverse sweep. A single to deep cover point.
leans forward to tickle it to square leg

oh he has come back to take out Yousuf. From round the stumps. It pitched full outside leg, just short of the popping crease, Yousuf tried to sweep it fine, missed and the ball spun in sharply to disturb the furniture.
still from round the stumps, turns outside off, cut to cover point
full and on the middle, driven to long-off for a single
goes over the wicket to Misbah. A googly and punched off the back foot to long-on
goes round the stumps to Younis, on the middle and leg, straightens and defended cautiously down the track
turns towards middle, pushed back down the wicket.
almost caught by Sehwag. It floated in towards off and middle, Misbah punched it in the air back to Sehwag who lunged but it fell just short.
short of length, forced to long-on
super sweep. Another favourite of his. He went down on his knee and found the deep backward square leg boundary
leans forward to push to midwicket
fuller, on driven to long-on
shuffles towards middle and works a delivery turning into middle behind square leg
Chawla goes round the stumps for Misbah as well. It spun across Misbah who tried to guide it with the turn to cover point and is beaten
fuller and driven down to long-on
There comes the sweep. The conventional one. Fetched from outside off to deep midwicket

lands on a length outside leg, turns in, Misbah goes right back to deflect it behind square. The long leg fielder (Gambhir) rushes in and fires in a throw to Dhoni who breaks the stumps.  Misbah is just in. The throw was a tad wide.
goes right back to punch a back of length delivery turning in from outside leg to long-on
flighted full, on the off and middle line, driven to long-off
gets forward to work a flighted ball to midwicket
sharp turn and Younis is beaten. It landed short of a driveable length and spun in past the prod and brushed the pad en route to Dhoni
fuller, turned through midwicket
short in length, flat and outside off, dabbed to right of point
low full toss outside off stump, dipping, swept to deep midwicket
leans forward to drive to long-on
back over the wicket. Really full delivery on middle, whipped to midwicket
lands it full and outside leg, just short of the popping crease, Younis went for the sweep but gloved it to the on side.
Super shot. He cleared the front foot, opened his stance and smashed a full delivery on leg stump to wide midwicket boundary
turning towards off, guided to cover point
back over the wickets. Flat and turning away after landing on off, left alone
quick, flat, googly, Misbah goes back to tickle it to square leg
Misbah pulls out the slog sweep. Down on his knee and swung a flighted delivery over midwicket. Pakistan gallop ahead.
on the back foot, worked to square leg
turning towards middle and leg, wristed past square leg. 200 up for Pakistan. They are in a great position here to win this one.
on the middle, turning, deflected to square leg
paddles from off and middle to fine leg for a single
Younis opts for his favourite sweep shot. He fetched it from well outside off and dragged it past the square-leg fielder and to the boundary. Drinks break.
leans forward to defend a flighted delivery on the off stump
turns it from the middle stump to square leg for a single
lands it outside leg and Younis takes up the challenge and sweeps to deep backward square leg region
Another sweep. From the middle stump to long leg.
from over the stumps, lands it outside off stump, a touch short, cut to deep point region
back round. Yet another sweep. Chawla has stationed a man at short fine leg, hoping for the top edge. Younis is repeatedly taken the challenge and has swept well
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
similar line, a touch slower through the air, swept to long leg
quicker, straighter, on the middle and off, nudged around the corner to backward square leg
on the middle, full,turning in,  flicked to long leg
around off stump line, picked off the turn to square leg 50 of the partnership up
goes right back to work it past midwicket. Sensible cricket.
from round the stumps, floated outside off and you guessed it, Younis plays another sweep shot. Super exhibition this.
Even better. Massive slog sweep. Younis Khan take a bow. He cleared the front foot, went down on his knees and proposed. Disposed it over wide midwicket. Shooper.
leans forward to drive to long-off
dabbed to cover point for a single.
aha! another sweep shot, this time a single to long leg. Those Indian fans who watched the 1987 Reliance World cup match between India and England would be getting the same sinking sweeping feeling!
leans forward to defend to the off side
full and on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket
on a length, around the off stump, played with soft hands, close on the off side and they cross over for a single
short in length, cuts in to beat the waft and strikes the pad but outside the off stump. Ishant shouts out an lbw appeal
kicks up from back of length, just outside off, steered to backward point
lands on a length, just outside off, cuts in, defended to the on side
fuller, on the middle and leg, wristed to Praveen Kumar at long leg
slower one outside off stump, caressed through extra cover
on the legs, a single past square leg
slower one full and outside off stump, sliced to wide third man
walks towards off stump, Irfan pushes it further across him and Misbah lets it go through
And so Misbah walks well outside off stump and whips a full delivery on the off to wide midwicket boundary. He saw the gap there and walked across.
short and on the leg stump line, moves towards middle and pulls it down to fine-leg boundary. The captain is doing his job
leans forward to push to covers for a single
banged in short, on the off stump line, dabbed towards cover point for a quick single. Younis Khan called him over for that and Misbah, after reaching the other end, gives him the thumbs up sign
short in length, outside off stump, cut to backward point
bouncer outside off stump, sways away from the line. He then practises the upper cut
Ishant gives him the chance to try that upper cut with another high bouncer, Younis gets his bat above his head but dabs it down to backward point. Fumble by Raina there.
fuller, straighter, Misbah shuffles to work it to deep midwicket
full and well outside the off stump, driven to sweeper cover
full and on the middle, driven back to Irfan
walks down the track, Irfan fires in a bouncer just down leg, Younis misses the pull and Dhoni gathers.
well outside the off stump, full, Younis doesn't move towards the line, just reaches out from his position and drives to sweeper cover
again full and wide, driven to deep cover
from round the stumps, pushed to cover point for a single.
appeal for a catch down leg. It went with the angle from round the stumps, Misbah tried to clip it away and it must have gone off the thigh pad.
full and on the middle and leg, flicked to long leg
goes back to clip a delivery turning into middle to square leg
leans forward to drive to long-on. Dhoni is not happy with the wild throw.
eased to long on for a single
leans forward to turn to midwicket
on the front foot and defended to midwicket
on the middle stump line, deflected to Yuvraj at midwicket
short and wide, reaches his ton with a super cut shot. He reaches the other end and does push ups! Misbah is laughing as he hugs him. YOunis has a even bigger smile.
another short-pitched delivery , pulled to square leg region
tries to work a length delivery on the pads, misses and it bounds off the pad
Super pull shot. Misbah rocks back to smash a throat-high bouncer to deep backward square leg boundary
short and outside off, Misbah carves it to deep backward point boundary. Lovely late cut. 50 for the captain. Fab chase this. Superbly controlled by Pakistan.
yorker on the leg and middle, strikes the pad. And a free hit coming up. The crowd roar.
caught at midwicket by Sehwag but obviously not out as it's a free hit. It was banged in short and Younis went for the pull but the bottom-hand came off the handle and he mistimed the shot
rushing through the channel outside off, left alone
fuller, on the middle and off, worked to deep square leg region
leans forward to drive crisply to left of mid-on

super shot to backward point boundary. It was short and well outside off, Misbah moved back and across, shifted his weight to the back leg, lifted his front and cut it up and over. Danny Morrison, rightly, says it reminds him of the Steve Waugh cut
driven to mid-on
from round the stumps, on a length ,coming in towards middle and off, punched on the up to Irfan
fullish delivery outside off, driven to long-off
well outside off stump, steered to backward point
slower, full, driven to long-off
short of length delivery, coming in from round the stumps, mistimes a pull to wide midwicket
fuller, on the middle and Misbah works it to long leg
short in length, on the middle and off, guided to backward point
around the off stump, steered to backward point
slower one, on the middle stump line, whipped to deep square leg
walks down the track, Praveen hurls it short and Younis pulls imperiously to wide midwicket boundary. Not enough pace to trouble Younis
slower one, full, pushed to the off side
on the middle and leg, straight, turned to deep square leg
short and climbing around off, Misbah walks towards off and pulls it down to deep square leg. Very well played.
Younis walks down and towards off, Irfan, from round the stumps, pushes it outside off and Younis flashes it to the cover boundary.
stays at his original position and whips a full delivery on middle and off to Yuvraj at midwicket
just outside off stump, guided to Raina at point
on the middle, turned t o midwicket
on a length, dabbed to right of midwicket
short of length, just outside off stump, steered to point
full, on the middle, Misbah takes out the front leg from the line and wallops it to to wide long-on boundary. They had a mid-on in.
on the middle, shuffles to middle stump line and clips it to long leg
slower one, off cutter, turned behind square leg for couple of runs 300 up for Pakistan.
outside the off stump, back of length, forced off the back foot to right of sweeper cover
on the leg and middle, flicks it in the air to deep midwicket.
on the off stump, no movement, driven to covers
yorker on the middle and off, driven to mid-on. One stroke away from a grand victory
Game over. Misbah drills a full pitched delivery through wide mid-on region. Fabulous chase. Very well controlled. Dhoni shakes hand with the batsmen, Yuvraj pats Younis Khan on the back.
